1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,291
In one of my first jobs, I worked closely with another young fellow,

2
00:00:04,320 --> 00:00:09,891
whom I'll call F.H. F.H. was like many persons you know.

3
00:00:10,081 --> 00:00:16,771
He was preoccupied with why he needed more money instead of being preoccupied with ways to make money.

4
00:00:17,039 --> 00:00:23,251
Each week, F.H. spent hours of company time working on his personal budget problems.

5
00:00:23,519 --> 00:00:29,811
His favorite topic of conversation was, I'm the most underpaid man here, let me tell you why.

6
00:00:30,561 --> 00:00:35,331
F.H. had the not uncommon attitude of, this is a big company,

7
00:00:35,360 --> 00:00:39,331
it's netting millions, it's paying a lot of people big salaries,

8
00:00:39,360 --> 00:00:41,490
so it ought to pay me more, too.

9
00:00:42,081 --> 00:00:46,211
F.H. had been passed over several times for pay increases.

10
00:00:46,320 --> 00:00:52,291
Finally, one day he decided that it was high time he went in there and demanded more money.

11
00:00:52,480 --> 00:00:56,691
About thirty minutes later, F.H. was back, all heated up.

12
00:00:56,800 --> 00:01:02,929
His expression made it obvious that next month's check would look exactly like this month's check.

13
00:01:03,519 --> 00:01:06,371
Immediately, F.H. began to let go.

14
00:01:06,641 --> 00:01:08,050
Boy, am I mad.

15
00:01:08,081 --> 00:01:12,450
What do you suppose the old man said when I told him I wanted more money?

16
00:01:12,641 --> 00:01:18,929
He had the gall to ask me, Why do you believe you are justified in asking for an increase?

17
00:01:19,360 --> 00:01:22,450
I gave him plenty of reasons, F.H. went on.

18
00:01:22,561 --> 00:01:27,090
I told him I'd been passed over when others around here were getting pay raises.

19
00:01:27,200 --> 00:01:30,929
I told him my bills are getting larger and my paycheck isn't.

20
00:01:30,960 --> 00:01:34,851
And I told him that I do everything around here they ask me to do.

21
00:01:35,200 --> 00:01:36,530
Can you beat that?

22
00:01:36,720 --> 00:01:44,771
I need a raise, but instead of paying me more, they give out raises to other guys around here who don't need it half as much as I do.

23
00:01:45,200 --> 00:01:50,291
Why, the way he acted, F.H. continued, you'd think I was asking for charity.

24
00:01:50,480 --> 00:01:56,130
All he would say is, when your record shows that you deserve more money, you'll get more money.

25
00:01:56,561 --> 00:01:59,570
Sure, I could do a better job if they paid me for it,

26
00:01:59,601 --> 00:02:02,771
but only a fool does something he isn't paid for.

27
00:02:03,760 --> 00:02:09,331
F.H. is an example of the breed that is blind to the how of making money.

28
00:02:09,519 --> 00:02:12,211
His last remark sums up his mistake.

29
00:02:12,320 --> 00:02:18,450
In effect, FH wanted the company to pay him more and then he would produce more.

30
00:02:18,720 --> 00:02:21,251
But this is not how the system works.

31
00:02:21,440 --> 00:02:25,010
You don't get a raise on the promise of better performance.

32
00:02:25,121 --> 00:02:28,771
You get a raise only by demonstrating better performance.

33
00:02:29,121 --> 00:02:33,411
You can't harvest money unless you plant the seeds that grow money.

34
00:02:33,519 --> 00:02:35,970
And the seed of money is service.

35
00:02:36,400 --> 00:02:40,691
Put service first and money takes care of itself.

